(firstQuint)Outcomes of Patients Not Responding to Antibiotics in the Community.

 To document and describe the clinical, microbiological, and pharmacoeconomic outcomes of two hundred patients who failed to respond to outpatient macrolide or beta-lactam therapy.

 Evaluable patients must have a positive culture obtained after they failed their initial macrolide or beta-lactam.

 The isolated pathogen must have a known MIC to the antibiotic class they failed to respond to (i.

e.

 macrolide or b-lactam).

 The isolate must be available to be sent to the central laboratory for MIC testing.

